&lt;p&gt;Thanks,&lt;/p&gt;
 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/100/how-can-i-move-a-workspace/?answer=101#post-id-101</link><description>The closes you can get is renaming the workspace with `rename workspace &lt;old_name&gt; to &lt;new_name&gt;` (see [userguide: renaming workspaces](http://i3wm.org/docs/userguide.html#_renaming_workspaces)). This is equivalent to moving everything there if the workspace doesn't exist yet, but otherwise you can focus parent a bunch of times and move that container.</description><pubDate>Sat, 09 Jun 2012 12:38:18 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/100/how-can-i-move-a-workspace/?answer=101#post-id-101</guid></item><item><title>Comment by joepd for &lt;p&gt;The closes you can get is renaming the workspace with &lt;code&gt;rename workspace &amp;lt;old_name&amp;gt; to &amp;lt;new_name&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; (see &lt;a href="http://i3wm.org/docs/userguide.html#_renaming_workspaces"&gt;userguide: renaming workspaces&lt;/a&gt;). This is equivalent to moving everything there if the workspace doesn't exist yet, but otherwise you can focus parent a bunch of times and move that container.&lt;/p&gt;
</title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/100/how-can-i-move-a-workspace/?comment=1000#comment-1000</link><description>For me, it works as of Version 4.4, also with unstacked/untabbed containers (it might have worked earlier). </description><pubDate>Tue, 08 Jan 2013 22:54:04 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/100/how-can-i-move-a-workspace/?comment=1000#comment-1000</guid></item><item><title>Comment by bruno.braga for &lt;p&gt;The closes you can get is renaming the workspace with &lt;code&gt;rename workspace &amp;lt;old_name&amp;gt; to &amp;lt;new_name&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; (see &lt;a href="http://i3wm.org/docs/userguide.html#_renaming_workspaces"&gt;userguide: renaming workspaces&lt;/a&gt;). This is equivalent to moving everything there if the workspace doesn't exist yet, but otherwise you can focus parent a bunch of times and move that container.&lt;/p&gt;
</title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/100/how-can-i-move-a-workspace/?comment=1081#comment-1081</link><description>Yep! Worked well!</description><pubDate>Fri, 18 Jan 2013 03:48:13 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/100/how-can-i-move-a-workspace/?comment=1081#comment-1081</guid></item><item><title>Comment by bruno.braga for &lt;p&gt;The closes you can get is renaming the workspace with &lt;code&gt;rename workspace &amp;lt;old_name&amp;gt; to &amp;lt;new_name&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; (see &lt;a href="http://i3wm.org/docs/userguide.html#_renaming_workspaces"&gt;userguide: renaming workspaces&lt;/a&gt;). This is equivalent to moving everything there if the workspace doesn't exist yet, but otherwise you can focus parent a bunch of times and move that container.&lt;/p&gt;
