&lt;p&gt;Thanks,&lt;/p&gt;
 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/100/how-can-i-move-a-workspace/?answer=102#post-id-102</link><description>I do it like this: 

Select the master container of the workspace by pressing $mod+a a few times. 

Then throw in your move command. The whole lay-out is replicated on the new workspace :) </description><pubDate>Sat, 09 Jun 2012 13:47:26 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/100/how-can-i-move-a-workspace/?answer=102#post-id-102</guid></item><item><title>Comment by Tucos for &lt;p&gt;I do it like this: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Select the master container of the workspace by pressing $mod+a a few times. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Then throw in your move command. The whole lay-out is replicated on the new workspace :) &lt;/p&gt;
</title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/100/how-can-i-move-a-workspace/?comment=112#comment-112</link><description>Turns out that you cannot move an entire workspace that way, so you'll have to somehow script your way around rename after all (unless you use workspace_layout stacked or so).&lt;sECuRE&gt; that’s just a limitation in the code (and the debug log says so)</description><pubDate>Sun, 10 Jun 2012 10:50:31 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/100/how-can-i-move-a-workspace/?comment=112#comment-112</guid></item><item><title>Comment by joepd for &lt;p&gt;I do it like this: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Select the master container of the workspace by pressing $mod+a a few times. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Then throw in your move command. The whole lay-out is replicated on the new workspace :) &lt;/p&gt;
</title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/100/how-can-i-move-a-workspace/?comment=114#comment-114</link><description>Apparently i just use this occasionally when the main container is tabbed or stacked. 

So, a hacky solution is this. Focus the main container with $mod+a, create a new xterm or whatever next to it, make this layout tabbed. Now you can throw the container around to another workspace. </description><pubDate>Sun, 10 Jun 2012 12:07:44 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/100/how-can-i-move-a-workspace/?comment=114#comment-114</guid></item><item><title>Comment by bruno.braga for &lt;p&gt;I do it like this: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Select the master container of the workspace by pressing $mod+a a few times. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Then throw in your move command. The whole lay-out is replicated on the new workspace :) &lt;/p&gt;
